{
  "question_id": "83aeda32-4bb9-4821-9be6-1a69fc5bf3f3",
  "short_text": "Square - 2 (For Loop)",
  "content": "Write a program that reads a number `M` and prints a **Square** of `M` rows and `M` columns using numbers.\n\n```\n1111\n2222\n3333\n4444\n```\n\n<MultiLineNote>\nUse **For** loop.\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `M`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `M` rows and `M` columns containing numbers as a **Square** shown in the sample output.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given number is `M = 4`,\n\n- Print the numbers on **4** rows and **4** columns as shown in the given image.\n\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/square-2.png' widthPercent='50'/>\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\n1111\n2222\n3333\n4444\n```\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "2ee058e0-c788-4cf3-aefa-045c0b38d5e3",
      "code_content": "number_of_rows = int(input())\n\nfor each_number in range(1, number_of_rows + 1):\n    row = str(each_number)\n    print(row * number_of_rows)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
